19:14.859 --> 19:16.121
What is she doing?

19:20.998 --> 19:22.727
I hate this place.

19:24.936 --> 19:26.699
Chris, what are you doing?

19:26.737 --> 19:27.897
Excuse us.

19:27.939 --> 19:30.336
I have perfect skin.
Perfect.

19:32.810 --> 19:34.940
- I think she's on something.
- Your food.

19:34.980 --> 19:37.671
I've decided that you are a waste

19:39.450 --> 19:42.010
of my perfect wardrobe

19:42.753 --> 19:45.722
with matching shoes.

19:46.690 --> 19:49.091
Chris, no one is that perfect.

19:52.096 --> 19:53.154
I am.

19:53.197 --> 19:55.158
And if you can't see that, I...

19:58.903 --> 20:00.837
feel sorry for you.

20:01.773 --> 20:02.773
Excuse me.

20:10.515 --> 20:11.573
Look at this!

20:13.518 --> 20:14.951
None of these plates match.

20:17.288 --> 20:19.552
No, Chris...

20:29.600 --> 20:31.090
I love this jacket.

20:31.135 --> 20:32.295
It's nice.

20:33.304 --> 20:34.304
Bye bye.

20:36.974 --> 20:39.772
Thank you so much.

20:40.912 --> 20:42.345
Everybody okay?

20:44.515 --> 20:47.450
She's got quite a temper there.

20:47.485 --> 20:51.546
Not usually, it must be the
curse of the fourth date.

20:52.857 --> 20:54.848
Just a theory of mine.

20:54.892 --> 20:57.554
I'm very sorry about this,
I'll be happy to replace everything.

20:57.595 --> 20:59.106
What was in this?
My name is Tom, by the way. Deal?

20:59.130 --> 21:01.428
- Tom Dill?
- Tom Bartlett. Did you use dill?

21:01.466 --> 21:03.597
- Like the pear.
- Send me the bill.

21:05.903 --> 21:07.564
- Rhymes with "dill", doesn't it?
- Yes.

21:08.906 --> 21:09.906
I will.

21:10.908 --> 21:12.168
That was a good one.

21:12.208 --> 21:14.248
I can't believe this happened.
This is very bizarre.

21:14.280 --> 21:16.480
Very sorry. I said that, didn't I?

21:16.514 --> 21:20.280
I should really go, I think.

21:20.318 --> 21:22.309
Here is my card.

21:22.353 --> 21:24.913
If you call me,
I'll replace the dishes and

21:26.157 --> 21:27.522
the meal.

21:28.659 --> 21:30.820
What is your name?

21:30.861 --> 21:32.852
Amanda. Shelton.

21:48.314 --> 21:49.740
- Tom...
- Lois

21:49.814 --> 21:52.044
What happened to you?
My god!

21:52.083 --> 21:55.416
I just had
the most incredible lunch.

21:55.453 --> 21:57.717
Too bad you didn't get
any of it in your mouth.

21:57.755 --> 21:59.655
No, no, no.
This is Chris's Lunch.

21:59.690 --> 22:01.351
She didn't take it too well, huh?

22:01.392 --> 22:02.791
She completely freaked out.

22:02.827 --> 22:07.594
And then she dumped me.
Which would have normally upset me

22:07.632 --> 22:12.064
if it wasn't for those
amazing crab things

22:12.104 --> 22:13.240
that made me feel...

22:13.640 --> 22:15.831
But you wanted to break up with her.

22:15.873 --> 22:19.309
No, Lois. I have feelings.
She treated me like I was nothing.

22:19.343 --> 22:22.073
I don't even know
if she have ever even really liked me.

22:23.848 --> 22:27.614
You know, she might have
just been using me.

22:28.552 --> 22:31.817
That's just terrible.

22:35.192 --> 22:38.355
I want to speak to the council
senior
as soon as the meeting is over.

22:38.396 --> 22:40.489
No, wait! How do I look?

22:40.531 --> 22:42.021
Come on, Lois. It's been two years.

22:42.066 --> 22:44.500
Jonathan is not biting.
You really should move on.

22:44.535 --> 22:46.696
I can't help it.
He makes me crazy.

22:46.737 --> 22:48.568
What do you see that I don't?

22:48.606 --> 22:49.971
It's his hands.

22:50.007 --> 22:52.601
They drive me wild.
I want them all over me.

22:52.643 --> 22:54.235
Come on, help me out.

22:54.278 --> 22:56.246
Every man has his weakness.
What's his?

22:56.280 --> 22:58.271
Jonathan's?
It's easy, immortality.

22:58.272 --> 22:59.992
His, not his grandfather's.
That's his flaw.

23:00.773 --> 23:02.773
Immortality?

23:09.528 --> 23:13.025
- Nice of you to join us.
- Sorry I'm late. Please, go on.

23:13.064 --> 23:16.266
Fine! Tom, you wanna tell me
why you spent 100.000 dollars

23:16.306 --> 23:17.967
on a floor that makes me dizzy?

23:18.402 --> 23:20.802
Place doesn't even look
like a restaurant.

23:20.838 --> 23:22.863
It's like something out of a MGM musical.

23:22.907 --> 23:25.205
Well, exactly. It is a stage for a fantasy

23:25.242 --> 23:28.439
and this floor will create the mood.
Sort of like a crab can...

23:31.282 --> 23:33.512
Jonathan's will be
the grandest restaurant in New York.

23:33.551 --> 23:36.213
It will be "Jonathan's".
And we want it to be lavish

23:36.253 --> 23:40.155
and sometimes you have to go the extra money
to get the extra dill... dollar.

23:40.191 --> 23:42.250
I don't like the sound of this.

23:43.260 --> 23:44.921
Have I ever let you down?

23:44.962 --> 23:48.693
Not yet. But you're young.
Very young.

23:48.733 --> 23:51.924
And don't forget. By exporting Jonathan's
to seven chains around the world

23:51.968 --> 23:54.066
there'll be Jonathan's everywhere.

23:54.105 --> 23:55.834
Royalties rolling in, articles about you

23:55.873 --> 23:58.842
in Vanity Fair, the Times...

23:58.876 --> 24:01.572
Not Henry. You.

24:01.612 --> 24:04.809
You will be immortal.

24:08.285 --> 24:09.946
I like you, Lois.

24:11.489 --> 24:13.150
You're like a man.

24:13.190 --> 24:15.158
You think with your nuts.

24:17.061 --> 24:18.528
Thank you, Jonathan.

24:18.562 --> 24:20.189
Alright, let's move on.

24:20.231 --> 24:21.231
Show me the fall catalog.

24:23.968 --> 24:26.860
